00046 bool
00047 DisassemblerX86::can_disassemble(SgAsmGenericHeader *header) const
00048 {
00049     SgAsmExecutableFileFormat::InsSetArchitecture isa = header->get_isa();
00050     if (isSgAsmDOSFileHeader(header))
00051         return 2==get_wordsize();
00052     if ((isa & SgAsmExecutableFileFormat::ISA_FAMILY_MASK) == SgAsmExecutableFileFormat::ISA_IA32_Family)
00053         return 4==get_wordsize();
00054     if ((isa & SgAsmExecutableFileFormat::ISA_FAMILY_MASK) == SgAsmExecutableFileFormat::ISA_X8664_Family)
00055         return 8==get_wordsize();
00056     return false;
00057 }

00060 DisassemblerX86::init(size_t wordsize)
00061 {
00062     switch (wordsize) {
00063         case 2: insnSize = x86_insnsize_16; set_registers(RegisterDictionary::dictionary_i286());  break;
00064         case 4: insnSize = x86_insnsize_32; set_registers(RegisterDictionary::dictionary_pentium4());  break;
00065         case 8: insnSize = x86_insnsize_64; set_registers(RegisterDictionary::dictionary_amd64()); break;

00073     /* Not actually necessary because we'll call it before each instruction. We call it here just to initialize all the data

00078 SgAsmInstruction *
00079 DisassemblerX86::disassembleOne(const MemoryMap *map, rose_addr_t start_va, AddressSet *successors)
00080 {
00081     /* The low-level disassembly function don't understand MemoryMap mappings. Therefore, remap the next few bytes (enough
00082      * for at least one instruction) into a temporary buffer. The longest x86 instruction is 15 bytes in 16-bit mode and 13
00083      * bytes in 32-bit mode:
00084      *
00085      * [16-bit]: 66 67 F0 3E 81 04 4E 01234567 89ABCDEF: add [ds:esi+ecx*2+0x67452301], 0xEFCDAB89
00086      * [32-bit]:       F0 3E 81 04 4E 01234567 89ABCDEF: add [ds:esi+ecx*2+0x67452301], 0xEFCDAB89
00087      *
00088      * In theory, by adding all appropriate prefix bytes you can obtain an instruction that is up to 16 bytes long. However,
00089      * the x86 CPU will generate an exception if the instruction length exceeds 15 bytes, and so will the getByte method. */
00090     unsigned char temp[16];
00091     size_t tempsz = map->read(temp, start_va, sizeof temp, get_protection());
00092 
00093     /* Disassemble the instruction */
00094     startInstruction(start_va, temp, tempsz);
00095     SgAsmx86Instruction *insn = disassemble(); /*throws an exception on error*/
00096     ROSE_ASSERT(insn);
00097 
00098     /* Note successors if necesssary */
00099     if (successors) {
00100         bool complete;
00101         AddressSet suc2 = insn->get_successors(&complete);
00102         successors->insert(suc2.begin(), suc2.end());
00103     }
00104 
00105     update_progress(insn);
00106     return insn;
00107 }

00187 X86InstructionSize
00188 DisassemblerX86::effectiveOperandSize() const
00189 {
00190     if (operandSizeOverride) {
00191         switch (insnSize) {
00192             case x86_insnsize_16:
00193                 return x86_insnsize_32;
00194             case x86_insnsize_32:
00195                 return x86_insnsize_16;
00196             case x86_insnsize_64: {
00197                 /* Some instructions (e.g., MOVD/MOVQ) have both the operandSizeOverride prefix (0x66) along with the REX.W
00198                  * bit. These instructions are inherently 32-bit and they use the REX.W bit to specify 64-bit operands. Also,
00199                  * for instructions that don't have 0x66 as part of the opcode but which are inherently 32-bit and use the
00200                  * REX.W bit to select 64-bit operands, the CPU seems to ignore extraneous 0x66 prefixes when REX.W is set. */
00201                 if (rexPresent && rexW)
00202                     return x86_insnsize_64;
00203                 return x86_insnsize_16;
00204             }
00205                         default: { ROSE_ASSERT(false); /* avoid MSCV warning by adding return stmt */ return insnSize; }
00206         }
00207     } else {
00208         X86InstructionSize s = insnSize;
00209         if (insnSize == x86_insnsize_64 && !rexW && !sizeMustBe64Bit)
00210             s = x86_insnsize_32;
00211         return s;
00212         /* FIXME: This doesn't handle all of the special cases */
00213     }
00214 }

00308 SgAsmx86Instruction *
00309 DisassemblerX86::makeInstruction(X86InstructionKind kind, const std::string &mnemonic,
00310                                  SgAsmExpression *op1, SgAsmExpression *op2, SgAsmExpression *op3, SgAsmExpression *op4)
00311 {
00312     SgAsmx86Instruction *insn = new SgAsmx86Instruction(ip, mnemonic, kind, insnSize, effectiveOperandSize(),
00313                                                         effectiveAddressSize());
00314     ROSE_ASSERT(insn);
00315     insn->set_lockPrefix(lock);
00316     insn->set_repeatPrefix(repeatPrefix);
00317     insn->set_raw_bytes(SgUnsignedCharList(&(insnbuf[0]), &(insnbuf[0])+insnbufat));
00318     insn->set_segmentOverride(segOverride);
00319     if (branchPredictionEnabled)
00320         insn->set_branchPrediction(branchPrediction);
00321 
00322     SgAsmOperandList *operands = new SgAsmOperandList();
00323     insn->set_operandList(operands);
00324     operands->set_parent(insn);
00325 
00326     /* If any operand is null, then the following operands must also be null because analysis assumes that the operand vector
00327      * indices correspond to argument positions and don't expect null-padding in the vector. */
00328     ROSE_ASSERT((!op1 && !op2 && !op3 && !op4) ||
00329                 ( op1 && !op2 && !op3 && !op4) ||
00330                 ( op1 &&  op2 && !op3 && !op4) ||
00331                 ( op1 &&  op2 &&  op3 && !op4) ||
00332                 ( op1 &&  op2 &&  op3 &&  op4));
00333 
00334     if (op1)
00335         SageBuilderAsm::appendOperand(insn, op1);
00336     if (op2)
00337         SageBuilderAsm::appendOperand(insn, op2);
00338     if (op3)
00339         SageBuilderAsm::appendOperand(insn, op3);
00340     if (op4)
00341         SageBuilderAsm::appendOperand(insn, op4);
00342 
00343     return insn;
00344 }

00378 /* At one time this function created x86-specific register reference expressions (RREs) that had hard-coded values for register
00379  * class, register number, and register position. These values had the same meanings across all x86 architectures and
00380  * corresponded to various enums in ROSE.
00381  *
00382  * The new approach (added Oct 2010) replaces x86-specific values with a more generic RegisterDescriptor struct, where each
00383  * register is described by a major number (formerly the register class), a minor number (formerly the register number), and a
00384  * bit offset and size (formerly both represented by the register position).  The idea is that a RegisterDescriptor does not
00385  * need to contain machine-specific values. Therefore, we've added a level of indirection:  makeRegister() converts
00386  * machine-specific values to a register name, which is then looked up in a RegisterDictionary to return a
00387  * RegisterDescriptor.  The entries in the dictionary determine what registers are available to the disassembler.
00388  *
00389  * Currently (2010-10-05) the old class and numbers are used as the major and minor values but users should not assume that
00390  * this is the case. They can assume that unrelated registers (e.g., "eax" vs "ebx") have descriptors that map to
00391  * non-overlapping areas of the descriptor address space {major,minor,offset,size} while related registers (e.g., "eax" vs
00392  * "ax") map to overlapping areas of the descriptor address space. */
00393 SgAsmx86RegisterReferenceExpression *
00394 DisassemblerX86::makeRegister(uint8_t fullRegisterNumber, RegisterMode m, SgAsmType *registerType) const
00395 {
00396     /* Register names for various RegisterMode, indexed by the fullRegisterNumber. The names and order of these names come from
00397      * Intel documentation. */
00398     static const char* regnames8l[16] = {
00399         "al",  "cl",  "dl",  "bl",  "spl", "bpl", "sil", "dil", "r8b", "r9b", "r10b", "r11b", "r12b", "r13b", "r14b", "r15b"
00400     };
00401     static const char* regnames8h[4] = {
00402         "ah",  "ch",  "dh",  "bh"
00403     };
00404     static const char* regnames16[16] = {
00405         "ax",  "cx",  "dx",  "bx",  "sp",  "bp",  "si",  "di",  "r8w", "r9w", "r10w", "r11w", "r12w", "r13w", "r14w", "r15w"
00406     };
00407     static const char* regnames32[16] = {
00408         "eax", "ecx", "edx", "ebx", "esp", "ebp", "esi", "edi", "r8d", "r9d", "r10d", "r11d", "r12d", "r13d", "r14d", "r15d"
00409     };
00410     static const char* regnames64[16] = {
00411         "rax", "rcx", "rdx", "rbx", "rsp", "rbp", "rsi", "rdi", "r8",  "r9",  "r10",  "r11",  "r12",  "r13",  "r14",  "r15"
00412     };
00413     static const char* regnamesSeg[6] = {
00414         "es", "cs", "ss", "ds", "fs", "gs"
00415     };
00416 
00417     /* Obtain a register name. Also, override the registerType value for certain registers. */
00418     std::string name;
00419     switch (m) {
00420         case rmLegacyByte:
00421             if (fullRegisterNumber >= 8)
00422                 throw Exception("register number out of bounds");
00423             if (fullRegisterNumber & 4) {
00424                 name = regnames8h[fullRegisterNumber % 4];
00425             } else {
00426                 name = regnames8l[fullRegisterNumber % 4];
00427             }
00428             registerType = BYTET;
00429             break;
00430         case rmRexByte:
00431             if (fullRegisterNumber >= 16)
00432                 throw Exception("register number out of bounds");
00433             name = regnames8l[fullRegisterNumber];
00434             registerType = BYTET;
00435             break;
00436         case rmWord:
00437             if (fullRegisterNumber >= 16)
00438                 throw Exception("register number out of bounds");
00439             name = regnames16[fullRegisterNumber];
00440             registerType = WORDT;
00441             break;
00442         case rmDWord:
00443             if (fullRegisterNumber >= 16)
00444                 throw Exception("register number out of bounds");
00445             name = regnames32[fullRegisterNumber];
00446             registerType = DWORDT;
00447             break;
00448         case rmQWord:
00449             if (fullRegisterNumber >= 16)
00450                 throw Exception("register number out of bounds");
00451             name = regnames64[fullRegisterNumber];
00452             registerType = QWORDT;
00453             break;
00454         case rmSegment:
00455             if (fullRegisterNumber >= 6)
00456                 throw Exception("register number out of bounds");
00457             name = regnamesSeg[fullRegisterNumber];
00458             registerType = WORDT;
00459             break;
00460         case rmST:
00461             name = "st(" + StringUtility::numberToString(fullRegisterNumber) + ")";
00462             registerType = LDOUBLET;
00463             break;
00464         case rmMM:
00465             name = "mm" + StringUtility::numberToString(fullRegisterNumber);
00466             break;
00467         case rmXMM:
00468             name = "mmx" + StringUtility::numberToString(fullRegisterNumber);
00469             break;
00470         case rmControl:
00471             name = "cr" + StringUtility::numberToString(fullRegisterNumber);
00472             break;
00473         case rmDebug:
00474             name = "dr" + StringUtility::numberToString(fullRegisterNumber);
00475             break;
00476         case rmReturnNull:
00477             return NULL;
00478     }
00479     ROSE_ASSERT(!name.empty());
00480 
00481     /* Now that we have a register name, obtain the register descriptor from the dictionary. */
00482     ROSE_ASSERT(get_registers()!=NULL);
00483     const RegisterDescriptor *rdesc = get_registers()->lookup(name);
00484     if (!rdesc)
00485         throw Exception("register \"" + name + "\" is not available for " + get_registers()->get_architecture_name());
00486 
00487     /* Construct the return value. */
00488     SgAsmx86RegisterReferenceExpression *rre = new SgAsmx86RegisterReferenceExpression(*rdesc);
00489     ROSE_ASSERT(rre);
00490     rre->set_type(registerType);
00491     return rre;
00492 }

00497     switch (so) {

00500         case x86_segreg_ds: return makeRegister(x86_segreg_ds, rmSegment);

00534 SgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression *
00535 DisassemblerX86::decodeModrmMemory()
00536 {
00537     ROSE_ASSERT(modregrmByteSet);
00538     SgAsmExpression* addressExpr = NULL;
00539     X86SegmentRegister defaultSeg = x86_segreg_ds;
00540     if (effectiveAddressSize() == x86_insnsize_16) {
00541         if (modeField == 0 && rmField == 6) {
00542             /* Special case */
00543             size_t bit_offset = 8*insnbufat;
00544             SgAsmValueExpression *ve = SageBuilderAsm::makeWordValue(getWord());
00545             ve->set_bit_offset(bit_offset);
00546             ve->set_bit_size(32);
00547             addressExpr = ve;
00548         } else {
00549             switch (rmField) {
00550                 case 0:
00551                     defaultSeg = x86_segreg_ds;
00552                     addressExpr = SageBuilderAsm::makeAdd(makeRegister(3, rmWord), makeRegister(6, rmWord));
00553                     break;
00554                 case 1:
00555                     defaultSeg = x86_segreg_ds;
00556                     addressExpr = SageBuilderAsm::makeAdd(makeRegister(3, rmWord), makeRegister(7, rmWord));
00557                     break;
00558                 case 2:
00559                     defaultSeg = x86_segreg_ss;
00560                     addressExpr = SageBuilderAsm::makeAdd(makeRegister(5, rmWord), makeRegister(6, rmWord));
00561                     break;
00562                 case 3:
00563                     defaultSeg = x86_segreg_ss;
00564                     addressExpr = SageBuilderAsm::makeAdd(makeRegister(5, rmWord), makeRegister(7, rmWord));
00565                     break;
00566                 case 4:
00567                     defaultSeg = x86_segreg_ds;
00568                     addressExpr = makeRegister(6, rmWord);
00569                     break;
00570                 case 5:
00571                     defaultSeg = x86_segreg_ds;
00572                     addressExpr = makeRegister(7, rmWord);
00573                     break;
00574                 case 6:
00575                     defaultSeg = x86_segreg_ss;
00576                     addressExpr = makeRegister(5, rmWord);
00577                     break;
00578                 case 7:
00579                     defaultSeg = x86_segreg_ds;
00580                     addressExpr = makeRegister(3, rmWord);
00581                     break;
00582                 default: ROSE_ASSERT(false);
00583             }
00584             switch (modeField) {
00585                 case 0:
00586                     break; // No offset
00587                 case 1: {
00588                     size_t bit_offset = 8*insnbufat;
00589                     uint8_t offset = getByte();
00590                     SgAsmValueExpression *wv = SageBuilderAsm::makeWordValue((int16_t)(int8_t)offset);
00591                     wv->set_bit_offset(bit_offset);
00592                     wv->set_bit_size(8);
00593                     addressExpr = SageBuilderAsm::makeAdd(addressExpr, wv);
00594                     break;
00595                 }
00596                 case 2: {
00597                     size_t bit_offset = 8*insnbufat;
00598                     uint16_t offset = getWord();
00599                     SgAsmValueExpression *wv = SageBuilderAsm::makeWordValue(offset);
00600                     wv->set_bit_offset(bit_offset);
00601                     wv->set_bit_size(16);
00602                     addressExpr = SageBuilderAsm::makeAdd(addressExpr, wv);
00603                     break;
00604                 }
00605                 default:
00606                     ROSE_ASSERT(false);
00607             }
00608         }
00609     } else {
00610         /* 32 or 64 bits */
00611         if (modeField == 0 && rmField == 5) {
00612             /* Special case */
00613             size_t bit_offset = 8*insnbufat;
00614             uint32_t offset = getDWord();
00615             addressExpr = makeAddrSizeValue(IntegerOps::signExtend<32, 64>((uint64_t)offset), bit_offset, 32);
00616             if (insnSize == x86_insnsize_64) {
00617                 addressExpr = SageBuilderAsm::makeAdd(makeIP(), addressExpr);
00618             }
00619         } else {
00620             if (rmField == 4) { /* Need SIB */
00621                 uint8_t sib = getByte();
00622                 uint8_t sibScaleField = sib >> 6;
00623                 uint8_t sibIndexField = (sib & 0070) >> 3;
00624                 uint8_t sibBaseField = sib & 7;
00625                 uint8_t actualScale = (1 << sibScaleField);
00626                 SgAsmExpression* sibBase = NULL;
00627                 if (sibBaseField == 5) {
00628                     switch (modeField) {
00629                         case 0: {
00630                             size_t bit_offset = 8*insnbufat;
00631                             uint32_t offset = getDWord();
00632                             sibBase = makeAddrSizeValue(IntegerOps::signExtend<32, 64>((uint64_t)offset), bit_offset, 32);
00633                             break;
00634                         }
00635                         case 1: {
00636                             sibBase = makeRegister((rexB ? 13 : 5), sizeToMode(insnSize));
00637                             defaultSeg = x86_segreg_ss;
00638                             break;
00639                         }
00640                         case 2: {
00641                             sibBase = makeRegister((rexB ? 13 : 5), sizeToMode(insnSize));
00642                             defaultSeg = x86_segreg_ss;
00643                             break;
00644                         }
00645                         default:
00646                             ROSE_ASSERT(false);
00647                     }
00648                 } else {
00649                     sibBase = makeOperandRegisterFull(rexB, sibBaseField);
00650                     if (sibBaseField == 4)
00651                         defaultSeg = x86_segreg_ss;
00652                 }
00653                 if (sibIndexField == 4 && !rexX) {
00654                     addressExpr = sibBase;
00655                 } else if (actualScale == 1) {
00656                     addressExpr = SageBuilderAsm::makeAdd(sibBase, makeOperandRegisterFull(rexX, sibIndexField));
00657                 } else {
00658                     addressExpr = SageBuilderAsm::makeAdd(sibBase,
00659                                                           SageBuilderAsm::makeMul(makeOperandRegisterFull(rexX, sibIndexField),
00660                                                                                   SageBuilderAsm::makeByteValue(actualScale)));
00661                 }
00662             } else {
00663                 addressExpr = makeOperandRegisterFull(rexB, rmField);
00664                 if (rmField == 5)
00665                     defaultSeg = x86_segreg_ss;
00666             }
00667             switch (modeField) {
00668                 case 0:
00669                     break; /* No offset */
00670                 case 1: {
00671                     size_t bit_offset = 8*insnbufat;
00672                     uint8_t offset = getByte();
00673                     SgAsmByteValueExpression *offsetExpr = SageBuilderAsm::makeByteValue(offset);
00674                     offsetExpr->set_bit_offset(bit_offset);
00675                     offsetExpr->set_bit_size(8);
00676                     addressExpr = SageBuilderAsm::makeAdd(addressExpr, offsetExpr);
00677                     break;
00678                 }
00679                 case 2: {
00680                     size_t bit_offset = 8*insnbufat;
00681                     uint32_t offset = getDWord();
00682                     SgAsmDoubleWordValueExpression *offsetExpr = SageBuilderAsm::makeDWordValue(offset);
00683                     offsetExpr->set_bit_offset(bit_offset);
00684                     offsetExpr->set_bit_size(32);
00685                     addressExpr = SageBuilderAsm::makeAdd(addressExpr, offsetExpr);
00686                     break;
00687                 }
00688                 default:
00689                     ROSE_ASSERT(false);
00690             }
00691         }
00692     }
00693     ROSE_ASSERT(addressExpr);
00694     X86SegmentRegister seg;
00695     if (segOverride != x86_segreg_none) {
00696         seg = segOverride;
00697     } else {
00698         seg = defaultSeg;
00699     }
00700     SgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression* mr = SageBuilderAsm::makeMemoryReference(addressExpr,
00701                                                                              makeSegmentRegister(seg, insnSize==x86_insnsize_64));
00702     return mr;
00703 }
00704 
00705 void
00706 DisassemblerX86::fillInModRM(RegisterMode rmMode, SgAsmType *t)
00707 {
00708     if (modeField == 3) {
00709         modrm = makeRegister((rexB ? 8 : 0) + rmField, rmMode, t);
00710     } else {
00711         isSgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression(modrm)->set_type(t);
00712     }
00713 }
00714 
00715 SgAsmExpression *
00716 DisassemblerX86::makeModrmNormal(RegisterMode m, SgAsmType* mrType)
00717 {
00718     ROSE_ASSERT(modregrmByteSet);
00719     if (modeField == 3) {
00720         /* Register */
00721         if (m == rmLegacyByte && rexPresent)
00722             m = rmRexByte;
00723         return makeRegister((rexB ? 8 : 0) + rmField, m, mrType);
00724     } else {
00725         SgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression* modrm = decodeModrmMemory();
00726         modrm->set_type(mrType);
00727         return modrm;
00728     }
00729 }
00730 
00731 SgAsmx86RegisterReferenceExpression *
00732 DisassemblerX86::makeModrmRegister(RegisterMode m, SgAsmType* mrType)
00733 {
00734     ROSE_ASSERT(modregrmByteSet);
00735     if (m == rmLegacyByte && rexPresent)
00736         m = rmRexByte;
00737     return makeRegister((rexR ? 8 : 0) + regField, m, mrType);
00738 }

00810 SgAsmExpression *
00811 DisassemblerX86::getImmJz()
00812 {
00813     uint64_t val;
00814     size_t bit_offset=8*insnbufat, bit_size=0;
00815     if (effectiveOperandSize() == x86_insnsize_16) {
00816         bit_size = 16;
00817         uint16_t val2 = getWord();
00818         val = IntegerOps::signExtend<16, 64>((uint64_t)val2);
00819     } else {
00820         bit_size = 32;
00821         uint32_t val2 = getDWord();
00822         val = IntegerOps::signExtend<32, 64>((uint64_t)val2);
00823     }
00824     uint64_t target = ip + insnbufat + val;
00825     SgAsmValueExpression *retval = NULL;
00826     switch (insnSize) {
00827         case x86_insnsize_16:
00828             retval = SageBuilderAsm::makeWordValue(target);
00829             break;
00830         case x86_insnsize_32:
00831             retval = SageBuilderAsm::makeDWordValue(target);
00832             break;
00833         default:
00834             retval = SageBuilderAsm::makeQWordValue(target);
00835             break;
00836     }
00837     retval->set_bit_offset(bit_offset);
00838     retval->set_bit_size(bit_size);
00839     return retval;
00840 }

00897 /*========================================================================================================================
00898  * Main disassembly functions, each generally containing a huge "switch" statement based on one of the opcode bytes.
00899  *========================================================================================================================*/
00900 
00901 /* Mostly copied from the old x86Disassembler.C version */
00902 SgAsmx86Instruction *
00903 DisassemblerX86::disassemble()
00904 {
00905     uint8_t opcode = getByte();
00906     SgAsmx86Instruction *insn = 0;
00907     switch (opcode) {
00908         case 0x00: {
00909             getModRegRM(rmLegacyByte, rmLegacyByte, BYTET);
00910             insn = makeInstruction(x86_add, "add", modrm, reg);
00911             goto done;
00912         }
00913         case 0x01: {
00914             getModRegRM(effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandType());
00915             insn = makeInstruction(x86_add, "add", modrm, reg);
00916             goto done;
00917         }
00918         case 0x02: {
00919             getModRegRM(rmLegacyByte, rmLegacyByte, BYTET);
00920             insn = makeInstruction(x86_add, "add", reg, modrm);
00921             goto done;
00922         }
00923         case 0x03: {
00924             getModRegRM(effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandType());
00925             insn = makeInstruction(x86_add, "add", reg, modrm);
00926             goto done;
00927         }
00928         case 0x04: {
00929             SgAsmExpression* imm = getImmByteAsIv();
00930             insn = makeInstruction(x86_add, "add", makeRegister(0, rmLegacyByte), imm);
00931             goto done;
00932         }
00933         case 0x05: {
00934             SgAsmExpression* imm = getImmIzAsIv();
00935             insn = makeInstruction(x86_add, "add", makeRegisterEffective(0), imm);
00936             goto done;
00937         }
00938         case 0x06: {
00939             not64();
00940             insn = makeInstruction(x86_push, "push", makeRegister(0, rmSegment));
00941             goto done;
00942         }
00943         case 0x07: {
00944             not64();
00945             insn = makeInstruction(x86_pop, "pop", makeRegister(0, rmSegment));
00946             goto done;
00947         }
00948         case 0x08: {
00949             getModRegRM(rmLegacyByte, rmLegacyByte, BYTET);
00950             insn = makeInstruction(x86_or, "or", modrm, reg);
00951             goto done;
00952         }
00953         case 0x09: {
00954             getModRegRM(effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandType());
00955             insn = makeInstruction(x86_or, "or", modrm, reg);
00956             goto done;
00957         }
00958         case 0x0A: {
00959             getModRegRM(rmLegacyByte, rmLegacyByte, BYTET);
00960             insn = makeInstruction(x86_or, "or", reg, modrm);
00961             goto done;
00962         }
00963         case 0x0B: {
00964             getModRegRM(effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandType());
00965             insn = makeInstruction(x86_or, "or", reg, modrm);
00966             goto done;
00967         }
00968         case 0x0C: {
00969             SgAsmExpression* imm = getImmByteAsIv();
00970             insn = makeInstruction(x86_or, "or", makeRegister(0, rmLegacyByte), imm);
00971             goto done;
00972         }
00973         case 0x0D: {
00974             SgAsmExpression* imm = getImmIzAsIv();
00975             insn = makeInstruction(x86_or, "or", makeRegisterEffective(0), imm);
00976             goto done;
00977         }
00978         case 0x0E: {
00979             not64();
00980             insn = makeInstruction(x86_push, "push", makeRegister(1, rmSegment));
00981             goto done;
00982         }
00983         case 0x0F: {
00984             insn = decodeOpcode0F();
00985             goto done;
00986         }
00987         case 0x10: {
00988             getModRegRM(rmLegacyByte, rmLegacyByte, BYTET);
00989             insn = makeInstruction(x86_adc, "adc", modrm, reg);
00990             goto done;
00991         }
00992         case 0x11: {
00993             getModRegRM(effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandType());
00994             insn = makeInstruction(x86_adc, "adc", modrm, reg);
00995             goto done;
00996         }
00997         case 0x12: {
00998             getModRegRM(rmLegacyByte, rmLegacyByte, BYTET);
00999             insn = makeInstruction(x86_adc, "adc", reg, modrm);
01000             goto done;
01001         }
01002         case 0x13: {
01003             getModRegRM(effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandType());
01004             insn = makeInstruction(x86_adc, "adc", reg, modrm);
01005             goto done;
01006         }
01007         case 0x14: {
01008             SgAsmExpression* imm = getImmByteAsIv();
01009             insn = makeInstruction(x86_adc, "adc", makeRegister(0, rmLegacyByte), imm);
01010             goto done;

01064             insn = makeInstruction(x86_pop, "pop", makeRegister(3, rmSegment));
01065             goto done;
01066         }
01067         case 0x20: {
01068             getModRegRM(rmLegacyByte, rmLegacyByte, BYTET);
01069             insn = makeInstruction(x86_and, "and", modrm, reg);
01070             goto done;
01071         }
01072         case 0x21: {
01073             getModRegRM(effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandType());
01074             insn = makeInstruction(x86_and, "and", modrm, reg);
01075             goto done;
01076         }
01077         case 0x22: {
01078             getModRegRM(rmLegacyByte, rmLegacyByte, BYTET);
01079             insn = makeInstruction(x86_and, "and", reg, modrm);
01080             goto done;
01081         }
01082         case 0x23: {
01083             getModRegRM(effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandType());
01084             insn = makeInstruction(x86_and, "and", reg, modrm);
01085             goto done;
01086         }
01087         case 0x24: {
01088             SgAsmExpression* imm = getImmByteAsIv();
01089             insn = makeInstruction(x86_and, "and", makeRegister(0, rmLegacyByte), imm);
01090             goto done;
01091         }
01092         case 0x25: {
01093             SgAsmExpression* imm = getImmIzAsIv();
01094             insn = makeInstruction(x86_and, "and", makeRegisterEffective(0), imm);
01095             goto done;
01096         }
01097         case 0x26: {
01098             segOverride = x86_segreg_es;
01099             insn = disassemble();
01100             goto done;
01101         }
01102         case 0x27: {
01103             not64();

01106         }
01107         case 0x28: {
01108             getModRegRM(rmLegacyByte, rmLegacyByte, BYTET);
01109             insn = makeInstruction(x86_sub, "sub", modrm, reg);
01110             goto done;
01111         }
01112         case 0x29: {
01113             getModRegRM(effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandMode(), effectiveOperandType());
01114             insn = makeInstruction(x86_sub, "sub", modrm, reg);
01115             goto done;
01116         }
01117         case 0x2A: {
01118             getModRegRM(rmLegacyByte, rmLegacyByte, BYTET);
01119             insn = makeInstruction(x86_sub, "sub", reg, modrm);

02674 SgAsmx86Instruction *
02675 DisassemblerX86::decodeOpcode0F()
02676 {
02677     uint8_t opcode = getByte();
02678     switch (opcode) {
02679         case 0x00: {
02680             getModRegRM(rmReturnNull, rmWord, WORDT);
02681             return decodeGroup6();
02682         }
02683         case 0x01:
02684             return decodeGroup7();
02685         case 0x02: {
02686             getModRegRM(rmWord, rmWord, WORDT);
02687             return makeInstruction(x86_lar, "lar", reg, modrm);
02688         }
02689         case 0x03: {
02690             getModRegRM(rmWord, rmWord, WORDT);
02691             return makeInstruction(x86_lsl, "lsl", reg, modrm);
02692         }
02693         case 0x04:
02694             throw ExceptionX86("bad opcode 0x0f04", this);
02695         case 0x05:
02696             return makeInstruction(x86_syscall, "syscall");
02697         case 0x06:
02698             return makeInstruction(x86_clts, "clts");
02699         case 0x07:
02700             return makeInstruction(x86_sysret, "sysret");
02701         case 0x08:
02702             return makeInstruction(x86_invd, "invd");
02703         case 0x09:
02704             return makeInstruction(x86_wbinvd, "wbinvd");
02705         case 0x0A:
02706             throw ExceptionX86("bad opcode 0x0f0a", this);
02707         case 0x0B:
02708             return makeInstruction(x86_ud2, "ud2");
02709         case 0x0C:
02710             throw ExceptionX86("bad opcode 0x0f0c", this);
02711         case 0x0D:
02712             return decodeGroupP();
02713         case 0x0E:
02714             return makeInstruction(x86_femms, "femms");
02715         case 0x0F: {
02716             /* 3DNow! (AMD Specific) */
02717             getModRegRM(rmReturnNull, rmReturnNull, NULL);
02718             uint8_t thirdOpcodeByte = getByte();
02719             char opcodestr[16];
02720             sprintf(opcodestr, "0x0f0f%02x", thirdOpcodeByte);
02721             if (thirdOpcodeByte < 0x80) {
02722                 /* Conversions */
02723                 switch (thirdOpcodeByte) {
02724                     case 0x0C: {
02725                         fillInModRM(rmMM, V4WORDT);
02726                         reg = makeModrmRegister(rmMM, V2FLOATT);
02727                         return makeInstruction(x86_pi2fw, "pi2fw", reg, modrm);
02728                     }
02729                     case 0x0D: {
02730                         fillInModRM(rmMM, V2DWORDT);
02731                         reg = makeModrmRegister(rmMM, V2FLOATT);
02732                         return makeInstruction(x86_pi2fd, "pi2fd", reg, modrm);
02733                     }
02734                     case 0x1C: {
02735                         fillInModRM(rmMM, V2FLOATT);
02736                         reg = makeModrmRegister(rmMM, V4WORDT);
02737                         return makeInstruction(x86_pf2iw, "pf2iw", reg, modrm);
02738                     }
02739                     case 0x1D: {
02740                         fillInModRM(rmMM, V2FLOATT);
02741                         reg = makeModrmRegister(rmMM, V2DWORDT);
02742                         return makeInstruction(x86_pf2id, "pf2id", reg, modrm);
02743                     }
02744                     default:
02745                         throw ExceptionX86(std::string("bad opcode ")+opcodestr, this);
02746                 }
02747             } else if (thirdOpcodeByte < 0xB7) {
02748                 /* Floating-point operations */
02749                 fillInModRM(rmMM, V2FLOATT);
02750                 reg = makeModrmRegister(rmMM, V2FLOATT);
02751                 switch (thirdOpcodeByte) {
02752                     case 0x8A: return makeInstruction(x86_pfnacc, "pfnacc", reg, modrm);
02753                     case 0x8E: return makeInstruction(x86_pfpnacc, "pfpnacc", reg, modrm);
02754                     case 0x90: return makeInstruction(x86_pfcmpge, "pfcmpge", reg, modrm);
02755                     case 0x94: return makeInstruction(x86_pfmin, "pfmin", reg, modrm);
02756                     case 0x96: return makeInstruction(x86_pfrcp, "pfrcp", reg, modrm);
02757                     case 0x97: return makeInstruction(x86_pfrsqrt, "pfrsqrt", reg, modrm);
02758                     case 0x9A: return makeInstruction(x86_pfsub, "pfsub", reg, modrm);
02759                     case 0x9E: return makeInstruction(x86_pfadd, "pfadd", reg, modrm);
02760                     case 0xA0: return makeInstruction(x86_pfcmpgt, "pfcmpgt", reg, modrm);
02761                     case 0xA4: return makeInstruction(x86_pfmax, "pfmax", reg, modrm);
02762                     case 0xA6: return makeInstruction(x86_pfrcpit1, "pfrcpit1", reg, modrm);
02763                     case 0xA7: return makeInstruction(x86_pfrsqit1, "pfrsqit1", reg, modrm);
02764                     case 0xAA: return makeInstruction(x86_pfsubr, "pfsubr", reg, modrm);
02765                     case 0xAE: return makeInstruction(x86_pfacc, "pfacc", reg, modrm);
02766                     case 0xB0: return makeInstruction(x86_pfcmpeq, "pfcmpeq", reg, modrm);
02767                     case 0xB4: return makeInstruction(x86_pfmul, "pfmul", reg, modrm);
02768                     case 0xB6: return makeInstruction(x86_pfrcpit2, "pfrcpit2", reg, modrm);
02769                     default: {
02770                         throw ExceptionX86(std::string("bad opcode ")+opcodestr, this);
02771                     }
02772                 }
02773             } else {
02774                 /* Extra integer operations */
02775                 switch (thirdOpcodeByte) {
02776                     case 0xB7:
02777                         getModRegRM(rmMM, rmMM, V4WORDT);
02778                         return makeInstruction(x86_pmulhrw, "pmulhrw", reg, modrm);
02779                     case 0xBB:
02780                         getModRegRM(rmMM, rmMM, V2DWORDT);
02781                         return makeInstruction(x86_pswapd, "pswapd", reg, modrm);
02782                     case 0xBF:
02783                         getModRegRM(rmMM, rmMM, V8BYTET);
02784                         return makeInstruction(x86_pavgusb, "pavgusb", reg, modrm);
02785                     default:
02786                         throw ExceptionX86(std::string("bad opcode ")+opcodestr, this);
02787                 }
02788             }
02789         }
02790         case 0x10: {
02791             switch (mmPrefix()) {
02792                 case mmNone:
02793                     getModRegRM(rmXMM, rmXMM, V4FLOATT);
02794                     return makeInstruction(x86_movups, "movups", reg, modrm);
02795                 case mmF3:
02796                     getModRegRM(rmXMM, rmXMM, FLOATT);
02797                     return makeInstruction(x86_movss, "movss", reg, modrm);
02798                 case mm66:
02799                     getModRegRM(rmXMM, rmXMM, V2DOUBLET);
02800                     return makeInstruction(x86_movupd, "movupd", reg, modrm);
02801                 case mmF2:
02802                     getModRegRM(rmXMM, rmXMM, DOUBLET);
02803                     return makeInstruction(x86_movsd_sse, "movsd", reg, modrm);
02804             }
02805         }
02806         case 0x11: {
02807             switch (mmPrefix()) {
02808                 case mmNone:
02809                     getModRegRM(rmXMM, rmXMM, V4FLOATT);
02810                     return makeInstruction(x86_movups, "movups", modrm, reg);
02811                 case mmF3:
02812                     getModRegRM(rmXMM, rmXMM, FLOATT);
02813                     return makeInstruction(x86_movss, "movss", modrm, reg);
02814                 case mm66:
02815                     getModRegRM(rmXMM, rmXMM, V2DOUBLET);
02816                     return makeInstruction(x86_movupd, "movupd", modrm, reg);
02817                 case mmF2:

02822         case 0x12: {
02823             switch (mmPrefix()) {
02824                 case mmNone:
02825                     getModRegRM(rmXMM, rmXMM, V4FLOATT);
02826                     if (modeField == 3) {
02827                         return makeInstruction(x86_movhlps, "movhlps", reg, modrm);
02828                     } else {
02829                         return makeInstruction(x86_movlps, "movlps", reg, modrm);
02830                     }

02833                     return makeInstruction(x86_movsldup, "movsldup", reg, modrm);
02834                 case mm66:
02835                     getModRegRM(rmXMM, rmXMM, DOUBLET);

02838                 case mmF2:

02840                     return makeInstruction(x86_movddup, "movddup", reg, modrm);
02841             }
02842         }
02843         case 0x13: {

02846                     getModRegRM(rmXMM, rmXMM, V4FLOATT);
02847                     requireMemory();

02849                 case mmF3:
02850                     throw ExceptionX86("bad mm prefix F3 for opcode 0x0f13", this);
02851                 case mm66:

02853                     requireMemory();

02855                 case mmF2:
02856                     throw ExceptionX86("bad mm prefix F2 for opcode 0x0f13", this);
02857             }
02858         }

02860             switch (mmPrefix()) {
02861                 case mmNone:
02862                     getModRegRM(rmXMM, rmXMM, V2FLOATT, V4FLOATT);
02863                     return makeInstruction(x86_unpcklps, "unpcklps", reg, modrm);
02864                 case mmF3:
02865                     throw ExceptionX86("bad mm prefix F3 for opcode 0x0f14", this);
02866                 case mm66:

02877                     return makeInstruction(x86_unpckhps, "unpckhps", reg, modrm);
02878                 case mmF3:

02899                 case mm66:

04843                     throw ExceptionX86("bad mm prefix F2 for opcode 0x0fee", this);
04844             }
04845         }
04846         case 0xEF: {
04847             switch (mmPrefix()) {
04848                 case mmNone:
04849                     getModRegRM(rmMM, rmMM, QWORDT);

04851                 case mmF3:
04852                     throw ExceptionX86("bad mm prefix F3 for opcode 0x0fef", this);
04853                 case mm66:
04854                     getModRegRM(rmXMM, rmXMM, DQWORDT);
04855                     return makeInstruction(x86_pxor, "pxor", reg, modrm);
04856                 case mmF2:
04857                     throw ExceptionX86("bad mm prefix F2 for opcode 0x0fef", this);
04858             }
04859         }
04860         case 0xF0: {
04861             switch (mmPrefix()) {
04862                 case mmNone:
04863                     throw ExceptionX86("bad mm prefix None for opcode 0x0ff0", this);
04864                 case mmF3:
04865                     throw ExceptionX86("bad mm prefix F3 for opcode 0x0ff0", this);
04866                 case mm66:
04867                     throw ExceptionX86("bad mm prefix 66 for opcode 0x0ff0", this);
04868                 case mmF2:
04869                     getModRegRM(rmXMM, rmXMM, DQWORDT);
04870                     requireMemory();
04871                     return makeInstruction(x86_lddqu, "lddqu", reg, modrm);
04872             }
04873         }

04881                 case mm66:

04886             }
04887         }

04893                 case mmF3:
04894                     throw ExceptionX86("bad mm prefix F3 for opcode 0x0ff2", this);
04895                 case mm66:

04951                 case mm66:

04954                 case mmF2:

05017                 case mm66:

05090 /* SSSE3 (opcode 0F38) */
05091 SgAsmx86Instruction *
05092 DisassemblerX86::decodeOpcode0F38()
05093 {
05094     // Get the third byte of the opcode (the first two were read by the caller (decodeOpcode0F())
05095     uint8_t opcode = getByte();
05096     switch (opcode) {
05097         case 0x00: {
05098             switch (mmPrefix()) {
05099                 /* Note that getModRegRM sets the states reg and modrm. Also, standard prefixed used in the manual, "mm"
05100                  * refers to "mmx" registers and "xmm" refers to "sse" registers. */
05101                 case mmNone:
05102                     getModRegRM(rmMM, rmMM, V2DWORDT);
05103                     return makeInstruction(x86_pshufb, "pshufb", reg, modrm);
05104                 case mmF3:
05105                     throw ExceptionX86("bad mm prefix F3 for opcode 0x0f3800", this);
05106                 case mm66:
05107                     getModRegRM(rmXMM, rmXMM, V4DWORDT);
05108                     return makeInstruction(x86_pshufb, "pshufb", reg, modrm);
05109                 case mmF2:
05110                     throw ExceptionX86("bad mm prefix F2 for opcode 0x0f3800", this);
05111             }
05112         }
05113         default:
05114             throw ExceptionX86("bad SSE3 opcode", this);
05115     }
05116 }

05118 SgAsmx86Instruction *
05119 DisassemblerX86::decodeX87InstructionD8()
05120 {
05121     getModRegRM(rmReturnNull, rmST, FLOATT);
05122     if (isSgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression(modrm)) {
05123         isSgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression(modrm)->set_type(FLOATT);
05124     }
05125     if (modregrmByte < 0xC0) { // Using memory
05126         switch (regField) {
05127             case 0: return makeInstruction(x86_fadd, "fadd",  modrm);
05128             case 1: return makeInstruction(x86_fmul, "fmul",  modrm);
05129             case 2: return makeInstruction(x86_fcom, "fcom",  modrm);
05130             case 3: return makeInstruction(x86_fcomp, "fcomp", modrm);
05131             case 4: return makeInstruction(x86_fsub, "fsub",  modrm);
05132             case 5: return makeInstruction(x86_fsubr, "fsubr", modrm);
05133             case 6: return makeInstruction(x86_fdiv, "fdiv",  modrm);
05134             case 7: return makeInstruction(x86_fdivr, "fdivr", modrm);
05135                         default: { ROSE_ASSERT(false); /* avoid MSCV warning by adding return stmt */ return NULL; }
05136         }
05137     } else { // Two-operand register forms
05138         switch (regField) {
05139             case 0: return makeInstruction(x86_fadd, "fadd",   makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05140             case 1: return makeInstruction(x86_fmul, "fmul",   makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05141             case 2: return makeInstruction(x86_fcom, "fcom",   makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05142             case 3: return makeInstruction(x86_fcomp, "fcomp", makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05143             case 4: return makeInstruction(x86_fsub, "fsub",   makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05144             case 5: return makeInstruction(x86_fsubr, "fsubr", makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05145             case 6: return makeInstruction(x86_fdiv, "fdiv",   makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05146             case 7: return makeInstruction(x86_fdivr, "fdivr", makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05147                         default: { ROSE_ASSERT(false); /* avoid MSCV warning by adding return stmt */ return NULL; }
05148         }
05149     }
05150 }

05152 SgAsmx86Instruction *
05153 DisassemblerX86::decodeX87InstructionD9()
05154 {
05155     getModRegRM(rmReturnNull, rmReturnNull, NULL);
05156     if (modeField < 3) {
05157         SgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression* mr = isSgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression(modrm);
05158         ROSE_ASSERT(mr);
05159         switch (regField) {
05160             case 0:
05161                 mr->set_type(FLOATT);
05162                 return makeInstruction(x86_fld, "fld", modrm);
05163             case 1:
05164                 throw ExceptionX86("bad ModR/M for x87 opcode 0xd9", this);
05165             case 2:
05166                 mr->set_type(FLOATT);
05167                 return makeInstruction(x86_fst, "fst", modrm);
05168             case 3:
05169                 mr->set_type(FLOATT);
05170                 return makeInstruction(x86_fstp, "fstp", modrm);
05171             case 4:
05172                 mr->set_type(BYTET);
05173                 return makeInstruction(x86_fldenv, "fldenv", modrm);
05174             case 5:
05175                 mr->set_type(WORDT);
05176                 return makeInstruction(x86_fldcw, "fldcw", modrm);
05177             case 6:
05178                 mr->set_type(BYTET);
05179                 return makeInstruction(x86_fnstenv, "fnstenv", modrm);
05180             case 7:
05181                 mr->set_type(WORDT);
05182                 return makeInstruction(x86_fnstcw, "fnstcw", modrm);
05183             default:
05184                 ROSE_ASSERT(false);
05185       }
05186     } else if (regField == 0 || regField == 1) { // FLD and FXCH on registers

05191             default: ROSE_ASSERT(false);

05195             case 0xD0: return makeInstruction(x86_fnop, "fnop");
05196             case 0xE0: return makeInstruction(x86_fchs, "fchs");
05197             case 0xE1: return makeInstruction(x86_fabs, "fabs");
05198             case 0xE4: return makeInstruction(x86_ftst, "ftst");
05199             case 0xE5: return makeInstruction(x86_fxam, "fxam");
05200             case 0xE8: return makeInstruction(x86_fld1, "fld1");
05201             case 0xE9: return makeInstruction(x86_fldl2t, "fldl2t");
05202             case 0xEA: return makeInstruction(x86_fldl2e, "fldl2e");
05203             case 0xEB: return makeInstruction(x86_fldpi, "fldpi");
05204             case 0xEC: return makeInstruction(x86_fldlg2, "fldlg2");
05205             case 0xED: return makeInstruction(x86_fldln2, "fldln2");
05206             case 0xEE: return makeInstruction(x86_fldz, "fldz");
05207             case 0xF0: return makeInstruction(x86_f2xm1, "f2xm1");
05208             case 0xF1: return makeInstruction(x86_fyl2x, "fyl2x");
05209             case 0xF2: return makeInstruction(x86_fptan, "fptan");
05210             case 0xF3: return makeInstruction(x86_fpatan, "fpatan");
05211             case 0xF4: return makeInstruction(x86_fxtract, "fxtract");
05212             case 0xF5: return makeInstruction(x86_fprem1, "fprem1");
05213             case 0xF6: return makeInstruction(x86_fdecstp, "fdecstp");
05214             case 0xF7: return makeInstruction(x86_fincstp, "fincstp");
05215             case 0xF8: return makeInstruction(x86_fprem, "fprem");
05216             case 0xF9: return makeInstruction(x86_fyl2xp1, "fyl2xp1");
05217             case 0xFA: return makeInstruction(x86_fsqrt, "fsqrt");
05218             case 0xFB: return makeInstruction(x86_fsincos, "fsincos");
05219             case 0xFC: return makeInstruction(x86_frndint, "frndint");
05220             case 0xFD: return makeInstruction(x86_fscale, "fscale");
05221             case 0xFE: return makeInstruction(x86_fsin, "fsin");
05222             case 0xFF: return makeInstruction(x86_fcos, "fcos");

05230 SgAsmx86Instruction *
05231 DisassemblerX86::decodeX87InstructionDA()
05232 {
05233     getModRegRM(rmReturnNull, rmReturnNull, DWORDT);
05234     if (modeField < 3) {
05235         switch (regField) {
05236             case 0: return makeInstruction(x86_fiadd, "fiadd", modrm);
05237             case 1: return makeInstruction(x86_fimul, "fimul", modrm);
05238             case 2: return makeInstruction(x86_ficom, "ficom", modrm);
05239             case 3: return makeInstruction(x86_ficomp, "ficomp", modrm);
05240             case 4: return makeInstruction(x86_fisub, "fisub", modrm);
05241             case 5: return makeInstruction(x86_fisubr, "fisubr", modrm);
05242             case 6: return makeInstruction(x86_fidiv, "fidiv", modrm);
05243             case 7: return makeInstruction(x86_fidivr, "fidivr", modrm);
05244             default: ROSE_ASSERT(false);
05245         }
05246     } else if (regField < 4) { // FCMOV{B,E,BE,U}
05247         modrm = makeModrmRegister(rmST);
05248         switch (regField) {
05249             case 0: return makeInstruction(x86_fcmovb, "fcmovb", makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05250             case 1: return makeInstruction(x86_fcmove, "fcmove", makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05251             case 2: return makeInstruction(x86_fcmovbe, "fcmovbe", makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05252             case 3: return makeInstruction(x86_fcmovu, "fcmovu", makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05253             default: ROSE_ASSERT(false);
05254         }
05255     } else {
05256         switch (modregrmByte) {
05257             case 0xE9: return makeInstruction(x86_fucompp, "fucompp");
05258             default: throw ExceptionX86("bad ModR/M value for x87 opcode 0xda", this);
05259         }
05260     }
05261     /* avoid MSCV warning by adding return stmt */
05262     return NULL;
05263 }

05265 SgAsmx86Instruction *
05266 DisassemblerX86::decodeX87InstructionDB()
05267 {
05268     getModRegRM(rmReturnNull, rmReturnNull, NULL);
05269     if (modeField < 3) {
05270         SgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression* mr = isSgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression(modrm);
05271         ROSE_ASSERT(mr);
05272         if (regField <= 3) {
05273             mr->set_type(DWORDT);
05274         } else {
05275             mr->set_type(LDOUBLET);
05276         }
05277         switch (regField) {
05278             case 0: return makeInstruction(x86_fild, "fild", modrm);
05279             case 1: return makeInstruction(x86_fisttp, "fisttp", modrm);
05280             case 2: return makeInstruction(x86_fist, "fist", modrm);
05281             case 3: return makeInstruction(x86_fistp, "fistp", modrm);
05282             case 4: throw ExceptionX86("bad ModR/M value for x87 opcode 0xdb", this);
05283             case 5: return makeInstruction(x86_fld, "fld", modrm);
05284             case 6: throw ExceptionX86("bad ModR/M value for x87 opcode 0xdb", this);
05285             case 7: return makeInstruction(x86_fstp, "fstp", modrm);
05286             default: ROSE_ASSERT(false);
05287         }
05288     } else if (regField <= 3 || regField == 5 || regField == 6) { // FCMOV{NB,NE,NBE,NU}, FUCOMI, FCOMI
05289         modrm = makeModrmNormal(rmST, NULL);
05290         switch (regField) {
05291             case 0: return makeInstruction(x86_fcmovnb, "fcmovnb", makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05292             case 1: return makeInstruction(x86_fcmovne, "fcmovne", makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05293             case 2: return makeInstruction(x86_fcmovnbe, "fcmovnbe", makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05294             case 3: return makeInstruction(x86_fcmovnu, "fcmovnu", makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05295             case 5: return makeInstruction(x86_fucomi, "fucomi", makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05296             case 6: return makeInstruction(x86_fcomi, "fcomi", makeRegister(0, rmST), modrm);
05297             default: ROSE_ASSERT(false);
05298       }
05299     } else {
05300         switch (modregrmByte) {
05301             case 0xE2: return makeInstruction(x86_fnclex, "fnclex");
05302             case 0xE3: return makeInstruction(x86_fninit, "fninit");
05303             default: throw ExceptionX86("bad ModR/M value for x87 opcode 0xdb", this);
05304         }
05305     }
05306     /* avoid MSCV warning by adding return stmt */
05307     return NULL;
05308 }

05310 SgAsmx86Instruction *
